eNCA's Nqobile Madlala has this story. #eNCA #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - The private security sector is threatening to leave many sites and areas unguarded if it goes ahead with a strike over wages. Twenty-three unions representing half a million workers in the private security sector are demanding an average 16% wage increase each year over three years. READ: People turn to private security as an alternative to SAPS: analyst Security companies and other employers are offering an average of 3.5%. Unions say they are approaching the CCMA for a strike certificate and have urged the companies to up their offer.  